VALUES (
  'Nozawa Onsen Village', 'nozawa-onsen', 'Japan', 'Nagano', 36.9225, 138.6256,
  'A charming traditional onsen village where the ski runs end right in town. Famous for its 13 free public hot springs and the Dosojin Fire Festival. One of Japan''s most atmospheric ski towns.',
  3500, 7000, 'https://nozawaski.com/en/',
  true, '¥25,000–¥45,000/month', 'Moderate', 'Ryokans, guesthouses, employer housing.',
  'Ski runs connect directly to village. Nozawa Onsen snow shuttle.', 'Village parking areas.', 'Nearest shinkansen station: Iiyama (25min bus). Tokyo ~2.5hr via shinkansen.', 'Mountain roads. Snow tyres essential.',
  '¥35,000–¥50,000/month', 'Small local shops and convenience stores.', '¥700–¥1,200. Excellent local food — try the oyaki (stuffed dumplings).',
  'Nozawa Onsen Ski Resort, ryokans, restaurants, ski schools.', 'Limited — mainly hospitality and tourism.',
  'Stay Bar, Kawakami Bar. Small but social scene.', 'Nozawa onsen restaurants, izakayas, noodle shops.', 'Limited facilities.', 'Small shops, ski hire, souvenir stores.', 'Dosojin Fire Festival (January — one of Japan''s wildest festivals), lantern festivals.',
  'Village clinic. Nearest hospital in Iiyama.', 'Emergency services available.',
  'Magical traditional Japanese atmosphere. Like stepping back in time with great skiing.', 'Growing international community, especially Australian.', 'Onsen soaking culture, izakaya nights, fire festival celebrations.',
  '-8°C to 0°C', 'Heavy snowfall — village gets buried.', 'Hiking, onsen tourism continues year-round.',
  'Early December.', 'Nozawa Onsen community groups.', 'The free public onsens are life-changing. The fire festival in January is a must-see — locals throw burning logs at each other.'
);
