  best_time_to_arrive, community_groups, insider_tips)
VALUES (
  'Whistler Village', 'whistler-village', 'Canada', 'British Columbia', 50.1163, -122.9574,
  'Whistler Village IS the resort — a pedestrian village at the base of Whistler and Blackcomb mountains. North America''s premier ski destination with world-class dining, nightlife, and year-round activities.',
  13000, 40000, 'https://www.whistler.com',
  true, 'CAD $800–$1,400/month shared; CAD $1,800+ solo', 'Extremely high — staff housing waitlists are common. Many workers live in shared houses or even vans.', 'Hostels (HI Whistler), Airbnb, staff housing lottery, shared rentals.',
  'Village is ski-in/ski-out. Free local bus system (WAVE). Bus to Squamish/Vancouver available.', 'Day lots available but parking is limited and expensive in village. Free park-and-ride lots.', 'Vancouver International Airport ~130km (2hr via Sea-to-Sky Highway).', 'Sea-to-Sky Highway is well-maintained but can be treacherous in winter storms.',
  'CAD $500–$800/week. One of Canada''s most expensive resort towns.', 'IGA Marketplace, Nesters Market. Good selection but premium prices.', 'CAD $15–$35. Incredible restaurant scene — everything from sushi to fine dining.',
  'Vail Resorts (mountain operations), Four Seasons, Fairmont, restaurants, retail, ski schools.', 'Massive hospitality sector, construction (ongoing development), retail, outdoor guiding.',
  'Garfinkel''s, Moe Joe''s, Buffalo Bills, Longhorn Saloon. Legendary nightlife.', 'Araxi, Sushi Village, Splitz Grill, Peaked Pies, El Furniture Warehouse. Hundreds of options.', 'Meadow Park Sports Centre (pool, gym, ice rink), CrossFit Whistler, yoga studios.', 'Full services — banks, pharmacy, outdoor gear shops, liquor stores.', 'World Ski & Snowboard Festival (WSSF), Crankworx (MTB), film festivals, live music.',
  'Whistler Medical Clinic, Whistler Health Care Centre.', 'RCMP, fire, ambulance, Whistler Search and Rescue.',
  'The gold standard of ski town culture. International, social, active, expensive. A rite of passage for seasonal workers worldwide.', 'Hugely international — Australian, British, Japanese, South American workers. English primary.', 'Non-stop social scene. Staff parties, bar nights, powder day sick calls, hiking, biking, lakes.',
  '-5°C to 3°C in village', 'Regular snowfall at village level (~650m elevation).', 'Top mountain biking destination. Hiking, zip-lining, golf, lake activities.',
  'Late October to mid-November for December start. Apply to Vail Resorts early (Aug/Sep).', 'Whistler Housing Crisis Facebook group, Whistler Community Forum.', 'Staff housing is gold — if your employer offers it, take it. The Sea-to-Sky highway is beautiful but respect it in winter. Get a Whistler Blackcomb staff pass.'
);
