VALUES (
  'Banff', 'banff', 'Canada', 'Alberta', 51.1784, -115.5708,
  'A stunning national park town in the Canadian Rockies. Base for Banff Sunshine, Lake Louise, and Mt Norquay. One of the world''s most beautiful mountain towns with incredible wildlife and scenery.',
  8000, 25000, 'https://www.banff.ca',
  true, 'CAD $700–$1,200/month shared. Staff housing common.', 'Very high — Banff housing is infamously difficult. Staff accom is essential.', 'Hostels (HI Banff, Samesun), staff housing, shared rentals.',
  'Free Roam bus to Sunshine and Lake Louise. Town is walkable.', 'Town parking available. Resort parking free.', 'Calgary International Airport ~130km (1.5hr).', 'Trans-Canada Highway well-maintained. Can be icy.',
  'CAD $400–$650/week', 'IGA, Safeway in Banff. More options in Canmore (20min).', 'CAD $15–$30. Good mix of restaurants.',
  'Banff Sunshine Village, Lake Louise Ski Resort, Fairmont Banff Springs, hotels, restaurants.', 'National park services, tourism, hospitality, retail.',
  'Wild Bill''s, Dancing Sasquatch, Rose & Crown. Great pub scene.', 'The Bison, Chuck''s Steakhouse, Magpie & Stump, Tooloulou''s. Wide range.', 'Banff Recreation Centre (pool, gym), Sally Borden Fitness.', 'Full town amenities — shops, banks, pharmacy, outdoor stores.', 'Banff Centre arts events, Banff Film Festival, SnowDays.',
  'Banff Mineral Springs Hospital, Banff Medical Centre.', 'RCMP, fire, ambulance, Parks Canada wardens.',
  'National park town with strict development controls — keeps it beautiful. International, outdoor-focused, wildlife-rich.', 'Very international — Australian, British, Japanese working holiday makers. English and some French.', 'Pub nights, hot spring visits, wildlife spotting, hiking, lake visits.',
  '-15°C to -3°C. Cold but dry.', 'Regular snowfall.', 'Stunning summer — hiking, canoeing, wildlife. Equally busy as winter.',
  'September–October for November start.', 'Banff Seasonal Workers Facebook group.', 'The hot springs are cheap and essential for sore muscles. Watch for elk in town — they''re everywhere. Canmore is cheaper if you have a car.'
);
