VALUES (
  'Revelstoke', 'revelstoke', 'Canada', 'British Columbia', 50.9981, -118.1957,
  'A real mountain town (not a resort village) with authentic BC character. The resort is 5 min from downtown. Known for massive snowfall, affordable living (by BC standards), and a tight-knit community.',
  8500, 14000, 'https://www.revelstoke.com',
  true, 'CAD $600–$1,000/month shared', 'High and growing — the town is booming.', 'Hostels, Airbnb, shared houses.',
  'Free shuttle to resort from downtown. 5min drive.', 'Free town and resort parking.', 'Kelowna Airport ~175km (2.5hr). Nearest major: Calgary ~420km.', 'Trans-Canada Highway. Can get heavy snow.',
  'CAD $350–$550/week', 'Save-On-Foods, small local shops.', 'CAD $12–$25. Excellent food scene for the size.',
  'Revelstoke Mountain Resort, hotels, restaurants, heli-ski operators.', 'Forestry, railway (CP Rail base), construction, hospitality.',
  'The Village Idiot, Craft Bierhaus, Monashees. Great local bar scene.', 'Woolsey Creek, La Baguette, Taco Club, The Modern Bakeshop.', 'Revelstoke Forum (pool, gym, arena), climbing gym.', 'Good town amenities — hardware stores, outdoor shops, basics.', 'Revelstoke Railway Museum, powder day celebrations, local music.',
  'Queen Victoria Hospital, medical clinics.', 'RCMP, fire, ambulance.',
  'Authentic mountain town vibes — locals, lifers, and seasonal workers blend together. Less touristy than Whistler.', 'Growing international community but still predominantly Canadian.', 'Tight-knit, pub-focused, outdoor-obsessed.',
  '-8°C to -1°C', 'Heavy snowfall — town gets proper winter.', 'Mountain biking, hiking, paddleboarding on Upper Arrow Lake.',
  'Late October–November.', 'Revelstoke Community Facebook groups.', 'The resort gets 12+ metres of snow annually — bring proper gear. The town has real character that corporate resort villages lack.'
